Last updated: 11/20/2014

ASSUMPTIONS:

We did not create the fake PGD, but in our vm_inspector we implemented
appropriate macros that traverse the PTEs on a contiguous mmap-ed memory.

Please use last commit in the 'lost_hope' branch.

MODIFIED/ADDED FILES:

- flo-kernel/arch/arm/include/asm/unistd.h
  defined expose_page_table syscall at position 378

- flo-kernel/arch/arm/kernel/calls.S
  added expose_page_table to syscall table at position 378

- flo-kernel/include/linux/syscalls.h
  defined the syscall expose_page_table

- flo-kernel/mm/mmap.c
  expose_page_table syscall implementation

- vm_inspector/vm_inspector.c
  the test program that prints out the fake pgd of the given pid

- flo-kernel/include/linux/expose_page_table.h
  header file for syscall

- flo-kernel/mm/mmap.c
  the implementation of the syscall

- vm_inspector/vm_inspector.c
  the implementation of the vm_inspector test program

- flo-kernel/mm/mremap.c
